            <p>+ Ἀνεπάε ἡ μα<lb/>καρία Ζηνοβία ῾Ρηγί<lb/>νου ἐτῶν ἔνδεκα <lb/>ἐν μηνὶ Δαισίῳ 
                    ἑν<lb/>δεκάτῃ <expan>
                  <abbr>ἰνδικτ</abbr>
                  <ex>ιῶνος</ex>
               </expan> ιβʹ <lb/>τοῦ ἔτους
                    υνθʹ +</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation"
              ana="#b1"
              xml:id="elus0020.translation"
              corresp="#elus0020.transcription">
            <p>The blessed Zenobia, daughter of Reginos, went to her rest, aged 11 years, on the
                    11th of Daisios, 12th indiction, year 459.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The face of the tombstone is horizontally chisel dressed, the back is amorphous and rough. The letters have red filling. The date, in the Arabian era, corresponds to May 31, 564 CE. The twelfth indiction began on September 1, 563 CE.</p>
         </div>
